In the model, N is assumed to denote the total population. The parameter β is the transmission relative rate from person to person, βW is the transmission relative rate from reservoir to person, k is the relative transmissibility of asymptomatic to symptomatic individuals, ω is the incubation relative rate, p is the proportion of asymptomatic individuals, γ is the infectious period relative rate of symptomatic individuals, γ’ is the infectious period relative rate of asymptomatic individuals, ε is the relative rate of the pathogen’s lifetime, c is the shedding rate of the asymptomatic comparing to the infectious, and μ is the pathogen shedding coefficient of infectious individuals. The equations of the model are as follows:
